snippet: Mayor Cory A. Booker of Newark defeated Steve Lonegan to take the New Jersey seat that Senator Frank R. Lautenberg held until he died in June.
abstract: Mayor Cory A Booker of Newark easily wins New Jersey's special Senate election; defeats Republican opponent Steve Lonegan to take seat that Sen Frank R Lautenberg held until his death, finally giving Booker rise to office that measures up to his national profile.

byline.contributor: Eli M. Rosenberg and Nate Schweber contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: Mayor Cory A. Booker of Newark defeated Steve Lonegan to take the New Jersey seat that Senator Frank R. Lautenberg held until he died in June.

headline.main: Booker, Winning Rocky Senate Bid, Gets a Job to Fit His Profile
headline.print_headline: Victorious in Rocky Senate Bid, Booker Gets Job to Fit His Profile
